legal.credit_line: © The Trustees of the British Museum

description.value: Gold penannular ear-ring: made in two halves from a thick sheet of gold, shaped and then soldered together. At either end of the pennanular loop a further small piece of sheet gold was added to give the impression that the ear-ring was not hollow. The exterior seam is hidden by an applied band in the form of a rope plaited from three fine wires of gold; the interior seam was not further obscured. As observed, it has one circular loop at the end of the plait for fixing.
